# AI Pipeline Architecture

## Service Structure
```
services/ai-pipeline/
  main.py              # FastAPI app entry point
  routers/
    audio.py           # WebSocket audio streaming
    notes.py           # Note generation endpoints
    billing.py         # Billing code suggestion
    ehr.py             # EHR integration endpoints
  services/
    transcription.py   # Deepgram client wrapper
    note_generator.py  # Claude API note generation
    billing_engine.py  # Billing code extraction
    ehr_client.py      # FHIR R4 client
  prompts/
    base.py            # Prompt building utilities
    soap_note.py       # SOAP note template prompt
    referral.py        # Referral letter prompt
    discharge.py       # Discharge summary prompt
  models/
    schemas.py         # Pydantic models for all request/response
  utils/
    auth.py            # JWT validation
    logging.py         # Structured logging (no PHI)
    encryption.py      # PHI encryption utilities
  tests/
    test_note_generator.py
    test_billing_engine.py
    test_transcription.py
```

## Transcription Pipeline
1. Browser sends audio chunks (WebM/Opus, 250ms) via WebSocket
2. Audio Service receives and streams to Deepgram Nova-3 Medical
3. Deepgram config: model="nova-3-medical", diarize=true, smart_format=true
4. Interim results sent to browser immediately (low latency feedback)
5. Final results accumulated into transcript segments
6. On disconnect: compile full transcript, store in database

## Note Generation Pipeline
1. Receive: transcript + template_id + specialty + patient_context
2. Load template structure from database
3. Build system prompt: role + specialty + template structure + rules
4. Build user prompt: transcript + context
5. Call Claude API with structured output (tool_use for JSON)
6. Post-process: validate medical terms, extract billing codes
7. Return structured note with sections

## Claude API Patterns
```python
# Always use structured output for consistent parsing
response = client.messages.create(
    model="claude-sonnet-4-5-20250514",
    max_tokens=4096,
    temperature=0.1,  # Low temp for medical accuracy
    system=system_prompt,
    messages=[{"role": "user", "content": user_prompt}],
    tools=[{
        "name": "generate_clinical_note",
        "description": "Generate a structured clinical note",
        "input_schema": note_schema
    }],
    tool_choice={"type": "tool", "name": "generate_clinical_note"}
)
```

## Prompt Engineering Rules
- NEVER let the model fabricate information not in the transcript
- Always include: "Only include information explicitly stated or clearly implied in the transcript"
- Flag uncertain items with [?] marker
- Include specialty-specific terminology guidance
- Few-shot examples in system prompt for consistent formatting
- Separate "extraction" (facts from transcript) from "formatting" (template structure)

## Error Handling
- Retry Claude API calls 3x with exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s)
- Deepgram reconnection on WebSocket drop (auto-retry 3x)
- All errors logged with request ID (no PHI in logs)
- Client receives structured error: {error: string, code: string, retryable: boolean}

## Performance
- Note generation target: < 10 seconds for standard consultation
- Transcription latency: < 500ms from speech to display
- Cache template prompts (they don't change often)
- Stream note generation to UI via SSE when possible
